Author: Aireil
Changelog:
- 2.0.6.0:
   Preliminary 6.2 update
   Fix a bug where an incorrect encounter would be displayed if it is from the same zone. If you added a DSR entry early, you may need to re-add it, because FF Logs changed the encounter id.
   API 7 update
- 2.0.5.0:
   Add swap groups, allowing you to dynamically change the layout in the main window.
   Adding encounters in the layout is now easier.
   Some other minor improvements.

Author: yomishino
Description:
This plugin detects certain objects/NPCs such as Aether Currents nearby and shows where they are by various ways, e.g. pointing to their locations on screen and notifying you in Chat.

Currently detects:
	- Aether Currents
	- Mob Hunt Elite Marks
	- Gathering Points
	- [Experimental] Quest-related NPCs/Objects 

Note: Because most objects/NPCs are not loaded when they are too faraway or when there are too many entities nearby (such as too many player characters), they will not be detected in this case.

Icon by Lumas Arkfrost
 (https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yomishino/MyDalamudPlugins/main/plugins.json)
Name: Aether Compass [TEST] [Aku API 7]
Punchline: Compasses that detect and mark certain nearby objects/NPCs
